         <div xml:id="alalal-d21119"><!-- l2d5dt1 -->
            <head xml:id="alalal-d21119-Hd1e99">Divisio Textus</head>
            <p xml:id="alalal-d21119-d1e101">
               <cb ed="#Bc" n="b"/>
               <lb ed="#Bc" n="7"/>DIVISIO TEXTUS.
</p>
            <p xml:id="alalal-d21119-d1e108">
               <lb ed="#Bc" n="8"/>
               <quote xml:id="alalal-d21119-Qd1e112"> Post haec consideratio adducit,
<lb ed="#Bc" n="9"/>etc. </quote>
               <lb ed="#Bc" n="10"/>Ista pars dividitur in duas: in 
qua<lb break="no" ed="#Bc" n="11"/>rum prima agitur de aversione et 
con<lb break="no" ed="#Bc" n="12"/>versione. In secunda autem de 
distin<lb break="no" ed="#Bc" n="13"/>ctione ordinum : et hac incipit in 
prin<lb break="no" ed="#Bc" n="14"/>cipio distinctionis IX, ibi, A, <quote xml:id="alalal-d21119-Qd1e128"> Post
<lb ed="#Bc" n="15"/>praedicta superest, etc. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="alalal-d21119-d1e134">
               <lb ed="#Bc" n="16"/>Prima harum dividitur in quatuor : in
<lb ed="#Bc" n="17"/>quarum prima ponitur aversio et 
con<lb break="no" ed="#Bc" n="18"/>versio. In secunda, qui fuerunt aversi,
<lb ed="#Bc" n="19"/>in sequenti distinctione, ibi, A, <quote xml:id="alalal-d21119-Qd1e144"> 
Pre<lb break="no" ed="#Bc" n="20"/>terea sciri oportet, etc.</quote> In tertia, de
<lb ed="#Bc" n="21"/>operibus eorum et potentiis ordinatis ad
<lb ed="#Bc" n="22"/>opera, in distinctione VII, ibi, A, <quote xml:id="alalal-d21119-Qd1e154"> 
Sz<lb break="no" ed="#Bc" n="23"/>pra dictum est quod Angeli, etc. </quote> In
<lb ed="#Bc" n="24"/>quarta, agit de apparitionibus eorum per
<lb ed="#Bc" n="25"/>assumpta corpora, ibi, <quote xml:id="alalal-d21119-Qd1e163"> Solet etiam in
<lb ed="#Bc" n="26"/>questione versari, etc., </quote> et ibi incipit
<lb ed="#Bc" n="27"/>distinctio VITI.
</p>
            <p xml:id="alalal-d21119-d1e172">
               <lb ed="#Bc" n="28"/>In hac autem distinctione sunt quatuor:
<lb ed="#Bc" n="29"/>quorum primum est, Quid aversio ? 
Se<lb break="no" ed="#Bc" n="30"/>cundum, Quo ut potentia sunt aversi et
<lb ed="#Bc" n="31"/>converst? ibi, B, <quote xml:id="alalal-d21119-Qd1e182"> Habebant enim omnes
<lb ed="#Bc" n="32"/>liberum arbitrium, etc. </quote> In tertia, dicit
<lb ed="#Bc" n="33"/>quid additum conversis, et aversis 
abla<lb break="no" ed="#Bc" n="34"/>tum sit, ibi, C, <quote xml:id="alalal-d21119-Qd1e192"> Si autem quaeritur,
<lb ed="#Bc" n="35"/>etc. </quote> In quarta queritur, Utrum 
merue<lb break="no" ed="#Bc" n="36"/>runt, vel merentur beatitudinem 
perce<lb break="no" ed="#Bc" n="37"/>piam ? ibi, G, <quote xml:id="alalal-d21119-Qd1e201"> Hic queri solet, etc. </quote>
            </p>
         </div>
